A 'Papilio paris' is a species of butterfly belonging to the Papilionidae family. 
It has a striking black and yellow coloration with blue markings on its wings. 
The wingspan of an adult 'Papilio paris' ranges from 6 to 8 centimeters. 
The texture of its wings is smooth and papery to the touch. 
These butterflies are commonly found in tropical rainforests of Southeast Asia and Indonesia. 
'Papilio paris' is a popular choice among butterfly enthusiasts and are often kept in butterfly houses or gardens. 
They are known for their swift flight and graceful aerial maneuvers.
